      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:26:27",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/26/477",
      "text": [
        " «نَعَمْ» قُلْتُ فَاثْنَانِ يُصَلِّيَانِ عَلَيْهَا قَالَ «نَعَمْ وَ لَكِنْ يَقُومُ اَلْآخَرُ خَلْفَ اَلْآخَرِ وَ لاَ يَقُومُ بِجَنْبِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.477 - Al-Yasa' ibn Abdullah al-Qummi asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about a man praying over a funeral alone.\nImam (as) replied: \"Yes, he may do so.\"\nI then asked: \"What if there are two people praying?\"\nThe Imam said: \"Yes, but one should stand behind the other, not next to him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
